    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-24T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-24T19:00:00-05:00" n="172"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.154/3327: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-24T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 24, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>245. Reference Embassy’s 287 of June 20, 8 p.m. and previous correspondence. Bill
                    extending current funds for construction of International Highway until June 30,
                    1945 and permitting transfer to Haiti at any time within next fiscal year<note
                        n="8" xml:id="d172fn8">An Act dated May 17, 1944 (Public Law No. 304, 58
                        Stat. 222) amended the original “Act to promote the Defense of the United
                        States” (approved March 11, 1941, 55 Stat. 31) to provide an extension of
                        Lend-Lease appropriations from June 30, 1944, to June 30, 1945.</note> has
                    received Congressional approval. Presidential approval pending but likely.
                    Department and Public Roads Administration nevertheless emphasize need for speed
                    by Dominicans in placing necessary equipment on road.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
